  "prompt": "Are humans reproducing like rabbits?",
  "response": "No, humans are not reproducing like rabbits. The reproductive rates of humans and rabbits are quite different. Rabbits can reproduce very quickly, with short gestation periods (around 30 days) and large litter sizes (typically 4-12 kits) multiple times a year. \n\nIn contrast, humans have much longer gestation periods (about 9 months), typically smaller family sizes, and many factors such as social, economic, and cultural considerations influence reproduction rates. Additionally, humans generally invest more resources and time into raising each child, which further differentiates human reproduction from that of rabbits.",
